10/14/2015, 11:40 PM - /\/â‚¬[]@: I knew the day would be different, i knew i would like it in anyway it turned.. But still the excitement kept me on my toes. 
After a night of party and chit chat, when i went to sleep, my tired body kept telling me i would not wake up the next morning. But there i was, up with the sun for the big day.
I got ready, walked out of the gate anxious to see it, the only thing that i have to share u with, the only other thing tht i would let to own you, the first surprise.
When i got onto the bike kept my hands on your shoulders, my mind was stuck at the thought of the delicacy that lay inside my bag, pure bliss,the second surprise.
Then came the passing trees, the rocky hill, tiny waterfalls, with the clouds beneath me and the cold freezing me, i couldnt help but think why i never travelled before.
Two got cups of cappuccinos and a chicken sandwich took half the table, the other half by a gorgeous peach dress i just became a proud owner of. If not a pretty dress, what else can become a perfect 3rd surprise.
The slight wayanad showers greeted us on our way to pookod lake, what i thought was the final surprise. Aftr Some quick stolen kisses, long walks and talks, and an unromantic boat ride , i was the happiest birthday girl i hve ever seen.
But no , you were not done. You knew no birthday was complete without a cake . And there came my last surprise for the day, a beautiful cake, filling lunch and some private time with you.
The ride back was all about the misty mountains, your warm back, a peaceful sleep, and heavy rains. But even after the sky cleared, my mind was clouded with the thought of having to let you go back.
If not thia birthday, if not this day, i dont knw what i will call a perfect day.. Thank you for a day that i wouldnt want to change or forget..

10/26/2015, 2:48 PM - /\/â‚¬[]@: Often, when we have a crush, when we lust for a person, we see only a small percentage of who they really are. The rest we make up for ourselves. Rather than listen, or learn, we smother them in who we imagine them to be, what we desire for ourselves, we create little fantasies of people and let them grow in our hearts. And this is where the relationship fails. In time, the fiction we scribble onto a person falls away, the lies we tell ourselves unravel and soon the person standing in front of you is almost unrecognisable, you are now complete strangers in your own love. And what a terrible shame it is. My advice: pay attention to the small details of people, you will learn that the universe is far more spectacular an author than we could ever hope to be.
- Beau Taplin

11/4/2015, 8:24 PM - /\/â‚¬[]@: If she asks you
If she asks you who I am, tell her. Tell her
because she is not starting a fire for an explanation but a confession.

If you tell her I was just a girl you dated
for a couple of years, she will only give you a hard time.
The hundreds of photos tagged in your outdated profile and the stack
of books with our names written will be her allies.

If you tell her I was an old friend, she will only hear
half of what you say. She will recall how you looked at places
with a tinge of regret and a shade of nostalgia. She will remember
how you skipped a certain song â€• a reminder of something youâ€™ll find an excuse
not to tell her every time the car radio is on.

If she asks you who I was, lie a little,
because she is not crossing the line for answers but for assurances.

Donâ€™t tell her how our lips played with poetry and how we dared
to dream under the light of the taciturn satellite. Skip the part where we
fought dragons together and how we named each otherâ€™s scars.

Reserve the fact that you still keep the letters, notes, old restaurant receipts under
your drawers and some tearstained thoughts at the back of your pillow. She doesnâ€™t need to know
why you reread past conversations or why your mother mentioned me at the family dining table
just to ask you what I have been up to.

Finally, if she asks you who I was to you, tell her you love her. Put her in the limelight
because she is testing you to pull the trigger pointed at her

But you wonâ€™t. Instead, you will tell her sheâ€™s beautiful to compensate
for the words you never had the guts to tell me. You will tell her sheâ€™s a keeper, for the hell of it.
You will tell her a poor research about human cells being replaced after seven years so that one day,
I will leave no trace on your body.

She will then forget that you mentioned my name while sleeping. She will wash the lipstick stains
on your bedsheets and remove the extra toothbrush in the shower. She will ignore the way you twitch
every time you hear a familiar author or my favorite curse word. She will fill the spaces
of your fingers and plaster kisses at the holes of your chest. She will replace every scent of me
with her own promises, insecurities, and mistakes.

She will do this. She will, because when she asked you about me,
she knew I was the ghost of the house. And at the back of your head, you wanted to tell her
that the damned no longer need saving. But by all means,
darling, she can try.

And what is renewed in that experience is an intensity of frustration, and an intensity of satisfaction. It is as if, oddly, you were waiting for someone but you didnâ€™t know who they were until they arrived. Whether or not you were aware that there was something missing in your life, you will be when you meet the person you want. What psychoanalysis will add to this love story is that the person you fall in love with really is the man or woman of your dreams; that you have dreamed them up before you met them; not out of nothing â€” nothing comes of nothing â€” but out of prior experience, both real and wished for. You recognize them with such certainty because you already, in a certain sense, know them; and because you have quite literally been expecting them, you feel as though you have known them for ever, and yet, at the same time, they are quite foreign to you. They are familiar foreign bodies.

Vellapallied (verb)

A word used to describe the action of inviting someone to a party and then requesting not to come for the same. 

Usage - I was Vellapallied from the house party yesterday.

2/4/2016, 10:34 PM - /\/â‚¬[]@: I was travelling and chanced upon a beautiful home. It made me feel like me. The sun reflecting off the freshly painted walls made my skin tingle. I thought to myself "this is the one". I moved in. I settled. I took care of every nook and corner.
Time passed. The paint started peeling off. The window panes had permanent dirt on it. The rood tiles bore the scars of time. 
I visited other houses. The new ones with the shiny roofs and fancy gardens tempted me. I started calculating in my head if i should move. How much will that set me behind financially? 
With these thoughts rambling in my head i returned home. The familiar smell of mould greeted me. A thousand memories that the house held came flooding back to me. I decided i should stay

.........................................  ................        

Njnangalude classil oru spy undayirunnu 
Nihkalenga aaya oru spy 
Enna nanavu maaratha mudiyil 
 cheerp ittu cheeki. 
 Vidernna kannukalil kannezuthi
 Pottu thotta sundheri aaya spy

Brandharaaya njnangalkku nere 
Nishabdhamayi viplam nayichaval,
Aaralum kanatheyum , chumbika pedaleyum nirashaaayaval
Kannerpozhichaval .... 

FAC inte snehathinayi vembal kollunnaval 
Avar eriyunna panthukal anusaranayode 
Kadichu konduvarunnaval
Avar vechu neetunna appa kashnaengal naaki edukkunnaval 
 ...
Nanni ulla spy
Oru paavam spy 

Ente snehathinte appavum veenjum pankittaval 
21 velli naanayengalkkayi ente sheenahathe kurishil eettiyaval 
Oru paavam spy

Njan chumbikka pedathe poya Nitte chuvaanna chundukalil Podiyunna rakthatill ,ente kannerinte, ente viyarppinte , 
uppu nunayunnaval 
Ente priyappetta spy

Ente mark sheetil nirayunna chuvappu varakal
 ninakkulla ente chumbhanengal aakatte 
 Kurishil eerumbol njnan podikkunna kannuveer thullikal ninakkulla ente. Sneeham aakette 
Ni peerunna paapa bhaarengalil 
Ninte Guru bakthi ninakku thanelekatte 

Oduvil marvichu poya ninte manasakhi 
Ninte kazhutjil murukunna 4 muzham kayar aakathirikkatte 
Ninakkayi njan praarthikkette
